// Regression: a bare (no explicit type arguments) type-qualified static
// method call on a class imported from another module -- Counter.
// fromDouble(5), not new Counter(...) or a same-file class -- now
// resolves correctly instead of crashing AST->FIR conversion ("'Counter'
// has no dominating parameter, DeclareLocal, or global constant": the
// bare class name lowered as a variable load instead of a static-call
// target, since it fell through to being misparsed as an ordinary
// instance method call on an IDENTIFIER named "Counter"). There's no
// syntactic way to tell a type-qualified call apart from an ordinary
// `variable.method()` call at this point (both are `IDENTIFIER .
// IDENTIFIER (`) without knowing whether "Counter" is a type or a
// variable, which isn't resolved until after import merge -- the parser
// falls back to this codebase's PascalCase-for-types naming convention
// in deferred-import mode.
//
// (classes_cross_module_helper.fire, the sibling module this test
// imports, exists solely to exercise this cross-module path.)
import @firescript/std.io.println;
import classes_cross_module_helper.Counter;

c: Counter = Counter.fromDouble(5);
println(c.val);

/* EXPECT
10
*/
